A cikin kwayoyin halitta, SARS-CoV-2 ya fi kama da SARS-CoV fiye da MERS-CoV.
Ta hanyar watsa kwayar electron microscopy, an gano SARS-CoV-2 a cikin wani ɓangaren epithelium na hanyoyin numfashi na mutum.
An gano ACE2 na ɗan adam a matsayin mai karɓar SARS-CoV-2 kamar SARS-CoV.
Duk da haka, sunadarin S na SARS-CoV-2 yana ɗaure da ACE2 na ɗan adam ya fi ƙarfin ɗaurewar da yake da shi ga sunadarin S na SARS-CoV, wanda ya dace da gaskiyar cewa SARS-CoV-2 yana haifar da kamuwa da cuta ba kamar kamuwa da SARS-CoV a cikin marasa lafiya ba.
SARS-CoV-2 na iya samar da sabon gajeren furotin wanda aka sanya shi da lambar orf3b da kuma furotin da aka sanya shi da lambar orf8.
Furotin na SARS-CoV-2 orf3b na iya taka rawa a cikin cutar cutar da kuma hana bayyanar IFNβ; duk da haka, orf8 ba shi da wani sanannen yanki ko motsi.
A ranar 18 ga Fabrairu, 2020, Zhou, et al. sun ba da rahoton cikakken tsarin ACE2 na mutum mai ƙirar ƙira a ƙuduri na 2.9 Å a cikin hadaddun tare da jigilar amino acid B0AT1.
Sun gano cewa hadaddun, wanda ke da buɗewa da rufewa, an tsara su don yin dimers kuma hadadden ACE2-B0AT1 na iya ɗaure sunadarai biyu na S, wanda ya zama hujja don ganewa da kamuwa da CoV.
B0AT1 na iya zama wata manufa ta magani a cikin ƙirar magunguna don hana kamuwa da cutar SARS-CoV-2.
Inang na asali da kuma na tsakiya
An san SARS-CoV da MERS-CoV sun samo asali ne daga ƙuda kuma kowannensu ya watsa zuwa ga mutane ta hanyar bison daji da raƙumi.
Ta hanyar kwatanta kwayar halitta ta SARS-CoV-2 da sauran CoVs, ana ɗaukar ƙwanƙwasa a matsayin asalin SARS-CoV-2 saboda sabon kwayar cutar ta kasance daidai da kashi 96% na CoVs masu kama da SARS na ƙwanƙwasawa guda biyu da ake kira bat-SL-CoVZX45 da bat-SL-CoVZX21.
Duk da haka, ba a san irin matsakaiciyar mai watsawa da ke taimaka wa kwayar cutar ta tsallaka shingen jinsin don ya kamu da mutane ba, kuma ba a bayyana hanyar watsawa ba.
